<fact>
    <statement>
        <p>
  Because every linear map <m>T:\IR^m\to\IR^n</m> has a linear combination
  of the variables in each component, and thus
  <m>T(\vec e_i)</m> yields exactly the coefficients of <m>x_i</m>,
  the standard matrix for <m>T</m> is simply an ordered list of
  the coefficients of the <m>x_i</m>:
  <me>
    T\left(\left[\begin{array}{c}x\\y\\z\\w\end{array}\right]\right)
      =
    \left[\begin{array}{c}
      ax+by+cz+dw \\
      ex+fy+gz+hw
    \end{array}\right]
  \hspace{2em}
    A
      =
    \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
      a &amp; b &amp; c &amp; d \\
      e &amp; f &amp; g &amp; h
    \end{array}\right]
  </me>
        </p>
    </statement>
</fact>

